From 5acadb59be149af21b857950ba5b7765605582b9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 14:32:54 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 8.7: re-land PR checkout flow + sticky-header fix
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

PR checkout (re-implementation of the previously-reverted Phase 8.7):

- IKrtGitService extended with jjNew, jjEdit, jjGitImport, getJjOpHead,
  jjOpRestore, gitStashPush, gitCheckout, gitFetchPullRequest,
  getJjStatus, getGitStatus. Main-process impl shells out via spawn().
- krtVcs.ts: getWorkspacePreFlight returns a discriminated union on
  vcs (jj | git) carrying current state for the dialog detail.
- krtSwitchResume.ts: IKrtSwitchResumeService stores at most one
  ResumeToken under krt.switchResume.v1 (APPLICATION/MACHINE) — single
  active switch v1.
- krtSwitchOps.ts: switchTo + returnFrom. jj path captures preSwitchOp
  before `jj new` (jj 0.40 has no `op undo`); git path stashes if
  dirty before `git checkout` and records previous branch.
- PR pane: "Check out" button (primary styling) appears when the
  workspace is registered for the PR's repo. Click runs preFlight →
  three-way confirm dialog (jj / git-clean / git-dirty) → switchTo →
  IFileService.resolve to nudge the explorer.
- "KRT: Forget Active PR Switch" command — escape hatch when a
  persisted token is stuck or predates a code change.

Sticky-header fix:

- `.krt-pr-diff-section` was using `overflow: clip`, which Chromium
  treats as establishing a scroll container for sticky purposes —
  meaning sticky headers pinned within the section instead of bubbling
  out to the outer .krt-pr-editor scroll. Switched to
  `clip-path: inset(0 round 6px)`: visual clip without affecting
  layout or sticky's anchor.

Status pill, close-pr cleanup prompt, and gh-CLI prCheckout helper
not in this patch — those were Phase 8.7 polish and can land
incrementally.
